'''布膠帶'''（{{lang-en|Duct tape}}），中文譯名或依其高強度特性譯為'''[[牛皮紙|牛皮]]膠帶'''，或依其諧音譯為'''「大」力膠帶'''，或稱'''鴨子膠帶'''、'''導風管膠帶'''、'''防水布膠帶'''等，是一種含有布層的感壓黏性膠帶，通常在外層包有[[聚乙烯|聚乙烯]]，使膠布具防水功效。一般綑成一卷，常用於大範圍場地作黏貼或定點標示作用。

==歷史==
「Duc'''t''' tape」（結尾是字母t）原稱「Duc'''k''' tape」（結尾是字母k），源自於「Cotton duck」，duck為荷蘭語doek[[盎格魯化|盎格魯化]]的變形，為一種比[[帆布|帆布]]更緊密編織的布料，材質多為[[棉|棉]]或[[亞麻|麻]]，抗拉耐磨，當時多用於製作鞋子與衣物。長條形的Cotton duck布料就叫Cotton duck tape，也用來包裹[[鋼|鋼]]纜或電[[導體|導體]]來防止鏽蝕或磨損，例如1902年，支撐[[曼哈頓大橋|曼哈頓大橋]]的鋼纜是先塗上亞麻籽油，再用duck tape布條包覆，最後才裝設定位。<ref name=OED1902>{{Cite web|url=http://eagle.brooklynpubliclibrary.org/Default/Scripting/ArchiveView.asp?skin=BEagle&AppName=2&GZ=T&BaseHref=BEG%2F1902%2F11%2F21&PageSize=3&enter=true&Page=15|title=''Brooklyn Daily Eagle''|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121017204729/http://eagle.brooklynpubliclibrary.org/Default/Scripting/ArchiveView.asp?skin=BEagle&AppName=2&GZ=T&BaseHref=BEG%2F1902%2F11%2F21&PageSize=3&enter=true&Page=15|archivedate=2012-10-17}} 21 Nov 1902 "Considering..that 100,000 yards of cotton duck tape must be wrapped around the cable with neatness and exactitude, it may be imagined that this method of cable preservation is quite expensive."</ref>
以上都還未加上黏膠層，不是現代意義上的「膠」帶，只是單純的棉布帶，所以包不緊。

在[[二戰|二戰]]期間的1943年，在軍械工廠工作的Vesta Stoudt寫給[[富蘭克林·D·羅斯福|羅斯福總統]]一封信，說明她在工廠負責包裝彈藥箱，但她認為彈藥箱當時的密封方式，讓士兵們很難在匆忙中打開它們，所以她創造了一種織物膠帶並加以測試過，可以減少彈藥箱的開箱時間。<ref>[http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1943/10/24/page/1/article/couldnt-keep-her-idea-down "Couldn't Keep Her Idea Down"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150506050728/http://archives.chicagotribune.com/1943/10/24/page/1/article/couldnt-keep-her-idea-down/ |date=2015-05-06 }}, 24 October 1943, Chicago Tribune</ref>此信得到了羅斯福總統的認可，並轉交到了[[戰時生產委員會|戰時生產委員會]]，委員會指派了[[Revolite|Revolite]]公司來開發這項產品，.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kilmerhouse.com/2012/06/the-woman-who-invented-duct-tape/ |title=The Woman Who Invented Duct Tape |last1=Gurowitz |first1=Margaret |date=June 21, 2012 |website=KilmerHouse.com |publisher=Johnson & Johnson |accessdate=10 January 2014 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111053805/http://www.kilmerhouse.com/2012/06/the-woman-who-invented-duct-tape/ |archivedate=11 January 2014 |df= }}</ref>最後開發出了一項可以用手撕而不需剪刀裁斷的產品。這個未命名的產品由Cotton duck布（耐用）、[[聚乙烯|聚乙烯]]（防水）、以及[[橡膠|橡膠]]為基底（穩定性）的灰色黏著物所製成。<ref name=Freeman2003>{{cite news |last=Freeman |first=Jan |title=Tale of the tape |newspaper=Boston Globe |date=March 9, 2003 |url=http://listserv.linguistlist.org/pipermail/ads-l/2005-July/052229.html |accessdate=June 24, 2005 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208072454/http://listserv.linguistlist.org/pipermail/ads-l/2005-July/052229.html |archivedate=December 8, 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref name=Jumbo>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kwLnBY7mLcIC&pg=PA10 |page=10 |title=The Jumbo Duct Tape Book |first1=Jim |last1=Berg |first2=Tim |last2=Nyberg |publisher=Workman Publishing |year=2000 |isbn=0761121102 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212151021/http://books.google.com/books?id=kwLnBY7mLcIC&pg=PA10 |archivedate=2013-12-12 |df= }}</ref><ref name=Inventions>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rVQfBSlAZvAC&pg=PA22 |pages=22–23 |first1=David John |last1=Cole |first2=Eve |last2=Browning |first3=Fred E. H. |last3=Schroeder |title=Encyclopedia of Modern Everyday Inventions |year=2003 |publisher=Greenwood Publishing |isbn=0313313458 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213155533/http://books.google.com/books?id=rVQfBSlAZvAC&pg=PA22 |archivedate=2013-12-13 |df= }}</ref><ref name=Manco>{{cite web |url=http://www.duckbrand.com/Duck%20Tape%20Club/history-of-duck-tape.aspx |title=History of Duck Tape |publisher=Duck Brand |accessdate=August 27, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120812084402/http://www.duckbrand.com/Duck%20Tape%20Club/history-of-duck-tape.aspx |archivedate=2012年8月12日 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Genericide: When a Brand Name Becomes Generic|url=http://www.cbc.ca/ageofpersuasion/episode/season-5/2011/05/06/season-five-genericide-when-a-brand-name-becomes-generic-1/|work=Age of Persuasion|publisher=CBC|accessdate=14 May 2011|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514150320/http://www.cbc.ca/ageofpersuasion/episode/season-5/2011/05/06/season-five-genericide-when-a-brand-name-becomes-generic-1/|archivedate=14 May 2011|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zFimLDoTkZQC&pg=PA18 |page=18 |last=Steele |first=Randy |title=Tale of the Tape |work=Boating |date=July 2003 |quote=In 1942 research scientists at Johnson & Johnson sandwiched a layer of mesh fabric—cotton duck—between a top layer of green polyethylene plastic and a bottom layer of rubber glue, and pressed them together. |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424075143/https://books.google.com/books?id=zFimLDoTkZQC&pg=PA18 |archivedate=2016-04-24 |df= }}</ref>此膠帶很容易貼撕，很快地就用於修復載具與武器上。<ref name=Jumbo/>這種膠帶當時製成消光[[橄欖綠|橄欖綠]]色。

軍人們稱這種膠帶為「Duck tape」<ref name=Forbes>{{cite journal |url=https://www.forbes.com/2006/03/14/tools-duct-tape_cx_de_0315ducttape.html |title=The Other Greatest Tool Ever |last=Ewalt |first=David M. |work=Forbes |date=March 15, 2006 |accessdate=August 27, 2012 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120911010636/http://www.forbes.com/2006/03/14/tools-duct-tape_cx_de_0315ducttape.html |archivedate=September 11, 2012 |df= }}</ref>，這個稱呼的來源有多種說法，包括：是由duck布做的膠帶；或因為其防水的特性就像鴨子羽毛一樣；甚至也有來自1942年的兩棲軍用載具[[DUKW|DUKW]]（發音為duck）的說法。<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zWzeKxSYaHIC&pg=PT31 |page=31 |last=Kruszelnicki |first=Karl |title=It Ain't Necessarily So... Bro |publisher=HarperCollins Australia |year=2010 |isbn=0730445267 |volume=8 |series=New Moments in Science |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214095029/http://books.google.com/books?id=zWzeKxSYaHIC&pg=PT31 |archivedate=2013-12-14 |df= }}</ref>

二戰後，這種布膠帶在五金行販售，作為居家維修使用。1950年代，此膠帶製成銀灰色，因其耐用、防水且黏性穩定的特點，常用來纏繞通風管道(duct)這種一般膠帶無法勝任的高低溫管路，<ref name=Forbes/>因此又有了「Duct tape」的稱呼。

==規格==
它的標準尺寸為<math>1{7 \over 8}</math>英寸，即約5厘米。常見的有黑色、銀灰色或啡色，但其他顏色的亦會生產。

